1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:30,000
DM: Welcome back to Aldara, everyone. Before we pick up where we left off, let me set the stage.

2
00:00:40,000 --> 00:01:05,000
DM: The kingdom of Aldara was founded three hundred years ago, at the dawn of the Second Age, by Corwin the Elder.

3
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:45,000
DM: Corwin was the grandfather of the man who sits the throne today, King Theron.

4
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:25,000
DM: The capital, Highmoor, is built on the white cliffs above the Gray Sea.

5
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:58,000
DM: Most of Aldara's grain comes from the Vale of Orin, inland to the south.

6
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:38,000
DM: Now, two hundred years ago, Aldara fought the War of the Dusk against the elves of the north.

7
00:03:55,000 --> 00:04:20,000
DM: The elven city of Vethran was burned to the ground in the last year of that war.

8
00:04:35,000 --> 00:05:00,000
DM: The surviving elves withdrew beyond the Frostspine Mountains, and no elf has set foot in Aldara since.

9
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:28,000
DM: The war is why every Aldaran town still keeps a watch-bell to this day.

10
00:05:40,000 --> 00:06:05,000
DM: You step into the Salt Hound, the only inn in Highmoor's lower city. The innkeeper, a one-eyed woman named Brisa, leans over the bar.

11
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:35,000
DM (as Brisa): You want my advice, travellers? Keep well clear of the old Corwin crypt.

12
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:58,000
DM (as Brisa): They say the founding king was no mortal man. Half-fae, my gran told me, and his whole bloodline cursed for it.

13
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:30,000
Player-Mara: Aldwin sets down her cup and answers her.

14
00:07:35,000 --> 00:08:00,000
Player-Mara (as Sister Aldwin): I was raised in the temple of the Dawnmother, up in Highmoor. The sisters took me in as a child.

15
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:28,000
Player-Mara (as Sister Aldwin): The War of the Dusk left me an orphan. The temple was the only home I ever had.

16
00:08:40,000 --> 00:09:05,000
DM: The throne room doors give way. King Theron is on his feet, reaching for the alarm bell.

17
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:45,000
Player-Tomas: Garrick doesn't hesitate. I hurl my dagger at the king. That's... a 23 to hit.

18
00:09:55,000 --> 00:10:15,000
DM: More than enough. The blade takes Theron in the throat.

19
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:50,000
DM: King Theron is dead before he strikes the marble floor. The throne of Aldara now sits empty, and Theron left no heir.

20
00:10:55,000 --> 00:11:08,000
Player-Mara: Gods. We just killed the king.

21
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:28,000
DM: Four palace guards pour in from the side passage. Everyone roll initiative.

22
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:42,000
Player-Mara: Initiative is a 14.

23
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:58,000
Player-Tomas: I got an 8. Ugh.

24
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:45,000
DM: Guards go first. The lead guard swings at Garrick — that's a 16 against your armor, it hits. Take 7 slashing damage.

25
00:12:50,000 --> 00:13:15,000
Player-Tomas: Down to 22 hit points. I swing back with my axe — 19 to hit.

26
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:40,000
DM: You drop him. Two guards still standing.

27
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:58,000
Player-Mara: I cast sacred flame on the nearest one.

28
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:32,000
DM: With the last guard down, you sprint for the servants' gate.

29
00:14:40,000 --> 00:15:00,000
DM: You slip out into the night and ride hard for the north road.

30
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:28,000
DM: Three days of cold travel bring you into the foothills, far from Highmoor.

31
00:15:40,000 --> 00:16:00,000
Player-Tomas: Wait, hang on — can I even use my reaction while I'm prone? Let me grab the book.

32
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:28,000
DM: Uh, hold on. Okay, being prone doesn't stop your reaction, it just gives disadvantage on the attack roll.

33
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:45,000
Player-Mara: Cool. Hey, did anyone actually order the food yet?

34
00:16:50,000 --> 00:17:00,000
DM: Pizza's on the way. Let's take five and pick it back up after the break.
